Task 27-94-00-810-870-A

REV

Failure of the SEC3  <  - (20170801)

Effective on: 001-999
Possible Causes

  • RELAY-SEC 3 ANN SPLY 41CE3

  • SEC-3 1CE3

  • wiring of the RLY SEC FAULT signal from the relay to the SEC3

  • FCDC-1 3CE1

  • FCDC-2 3CE2

  • wiring of the DSI 20/5 (SEC 3 FAILED) signals

  • wiring of the 28VDC GND signal

  • wiring of the SEC3 ENGAGED (DSI 04) signal

  • wiring of the PLD ACTIVATION (DSI 01) signal

  • wiring of the REVERSE LOCK AUTHORIZATION (DSI02) signal

  • wiring from the pins A/C1 and A/C3 of the pushbutton switch (5CE3) to the first terminal block

  • P/BSW-FLT CTL/SEC 3 (5CE3)

  • wiring of the DGO 03 signal

  • wiring of the PIN PROGRAM SEC3 (DSI 16) signal

  • wiring from the circuit breaker (21CE3) to the first terminal block

  • wiring from the SEC3 (1CE3) pin AC/2 for the COM part and pin AF/2 for the MON part to the circuit breaker (21CE3)

  • wiring from the SEC3 (1CE3) pin AC/2 for the COM part and pin AF/2 for the MON part to the circuit breaker (21CE3):

  • wiring of the DSI 33 signal

  • wiring of the DSI 33 and 34 signals

    B. Do the operational test of the SEC3 SEE AMM 27-94-00-710-001 REV
    to make sure that it does the servoing of its related surfaces.  < 
    (1) If the flight controls move in relation to the SEC3 servoing:
    (a) Remove the SEC3 SEE AMM 27-94-34-000-001 .
    (b) At the SEC3 receptacle, do a check of the resistance between pin AB/12K and pin AE/12A SEE ASM 27-92-05 .
    1 If the resistance is less than 280 ohms:
    a Remove the RELAY-SEC 3 ANN SPLY (41CE3)   SEE AIPC 27-92-08-03 .
    b REV
    Do a check of the resistance of the relay between pins X1 and X2.  <   < 
    •
    		REV < 

    REV

    If the resistance is less than 280 ohms:  < 

    . replace the RELAY-SEC 3 ANN SPLY (41CE3)   SEE AIPC 27-92-08-03

    . replace the SEC-3 (1CE3)   SEE AMM 27-94-34-400-001 .

    •

    If the resistance is between 280 and 400 ohms:

    . do a check and repair the wiring of the RLY SEC FAULT signal from the relay to the SEC3  SEE ASM 27-92-05

    . install the relay

    . replace the SEC-3 (1CE3)   SEE AMM 27-94-34-400-001 .

    a Remove the relay (41CE3).
    b REV

    . install the SEC3 SEE AMM 27-94-34-400-001 .

    •

    If the resistance is between 280 and 400 ohms:

    . do a check and repair the wiring of the RLY SEC FAULT signal from the relay to the SEC3  SEE ASM 27-92-05

    REV < 

    REV

    . install the SEC3 SEE AMM 27-94-34-400-001 .

    Install the SEC3  <  < SEE AMM 27-94-34-400-001 REV
    .  < 
    b Remove the FCDC-1 (3CE1)   SEE AMM 27-95-34-000-001 .
    •
    		REV < 

    if the SEC3 FAULT warning message stays in view, install the FCDC-1 (3CE1)   SEE AMM 27-95-34-400-001 REV

    and go to Para. c_.  < 
    •

    if the SEC3 FAULT warning message goes out of view, replace the FCDC-1 (3CE1)   SEE AMM 27-95-34-000-001 and SEE AMM 27-95-34-400-001 .
